{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 530 (PR #4044) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/4044.","id":"vf_857e343b6d8b6bf5","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #530: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $\\ell(N)$ be maximal such that in any finite set $A\\subset \\mathbb{R}$ of size $N$ there exists a Sidon subset $S$ of size $\\ell(N)$ (i.e. the only solutions to $a+b=c+d$ in $S$ are the trivial ones). Determine the order of $\\ell(N)$.\n\nIn particular, is it true that $\\ell(N)\\sim N^{1/2}$? Current best: Erd\\H{o}s noted the bounds\\[N^{1/3} \\ll \\ell(N) \\leq (1+o(1))N^{1/2}\\](the upper bound following from the case $A=\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$). The lower bound was improved to $N^{1/2}\\ll \\ell(N)$ by Koml\\'{o}s, Sulyok, and Szemer\\'{e}di \\cite{KSS75}. The correct constant is unknown, but it is likely that the upper bound is true, so that $\\ell(N)\\sim N^{1/2}$. Prize: no. OEIS: A143824. Tags: number theory, sidon sets.","id":"vf_a1b01dc98a135902","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/530.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_857e343b6d8b6bf5","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:530","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_857e343b6d8b6bf5","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_a1b01dc98a135902","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","